Female. General body coloration not observed, thorax uniformly heavily sclerotized. Head: nearly rounded in frontal view, vertex not enlarged, ratio of head length to width: 1.04 , setae alveoli patches extending anteriorly at midline, meeting supraocular alveoli patches. Frons without intra-ocular sutures. Eyes large, about twice the length of clypeus. Ratio of labrum length to head length: 0.60 ; ratio labrum length to flagellomere 1 length: 0.85 ; ratio of flagellomere 1 length to length of flagellomeres 2 + 3 : 1.11 (
